
# 15 MHz DDS Signal Generator Firmware Suite

This project is a high-performance, real-time frequency synthesis driver designed for **Raspberry Pi Pico (RP2040)** utilizing the **AD9833** Direct Digital Synthesis chip. 

This firmware manages real-time frequency tuning up to 15,000,000 Hz, duty-cycle shaping, and waveform outputs with clean signal synthesis.

---

## Technical Specifications
- **Frequency Range:** 0.1 Hz to 15.0 MHz (sub-Hz resolution limit)
- **Active Frequency:** `1,000,000 Hz`
- **Active Waveform:** `SINE`
- **Output Driver:** AD9833 Synthesis Logic
- **Build System:** CMake modern cross-compilation toolchain

---

## Wiring/Connection Architecture

Please connect the DDS board to the **Raspberry Pi Pico (RP2040)** according to the following hardware schematic layout:


| Target MCU Pin | Signal Description | AD9833 Module Pin | Notes |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **GPIO 19** | SPI Master-Out Slave-In (MOSI) | **SDATA / DATA** | Serial Data interface |
| **GPIO 18** | SPI Clock (SCK) | **SCLK / CLK** | Serial Clock interface |
| **GPIO 17** | Active-Low Chip Select (CS) | **FSYNC / FQ_UD** | Frame synchronization / load |
| **GND** | Comm ground reference | **GND** | Common ground reference |
| **3.3V / 5V** | Power rail | **VCC** | 3.3V for AD9833 / 5V for AD9850 |


*Ensure appropriate power filtering is enabled on VCC bypass capacitors to avoid RF ripple on output waves at high MHz frequencies.*

